{"type":"message","id":"62645651","parentId":"5a3e9e49","timestamp":"2026-04-10T09:11:12.448Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"1832\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"1830\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-04-10 09:11 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Nemesis (7924461837)\",\n  \"id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"name\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"username\": \"nemesis0008\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexu\",\n  \"body\": \"Gemini is overloaded right now. Let me do this properly from memory first, I'll get you the philosopher breakdown:\\n\\n───\\n\\nPhilosopher positions on this:\\n\\n1. Aristotle (384 BC): Said both are required for eudaimonia (the good life). Love without means is fragile, wealth without affection is empty. He explicitly warned against choosing one.\\n2. Epictetus: Warned that attaching your happiness only to money will destroy you, attaching it only to another person will also destroy you.\\n3. Schopenhauer: Brutally honest - almost all human suffering comes from choosing one over the other. He said people will regret both choices equally when they are old.\\n4. Marx: Observed that when money becomes the only measure, love itself becomes a commodity you can buy. Which is exactly what happens now.\\n5. Simone de Beauvoir: \\\"Love is not possible between people who do not first have the material security to be free to love.\\\"\\n\\n───\\n\\n✅ 100 word summary:\\nEvery major philosopher agreed there is no correct choice. There is only the mistake of choosing. The entire debate is a trap. No human ever thrived with only one. Love without security decays into resentment. Wealth without connection decays into loneliness. The only winning move is to never accept the choice at all. Anyone who asks you to pick one does not have your best interests at heart. That is the secret all of them arrived at, separated by 2400 years. 🖤\"\n}\n```\n\nWhat do the Bhagavad Gita and other Upanishads tell about this topic? Can you analyse all the Indian historical philosophers and rishis who have thought about it and let us know what's the summary of it in 100 words?"}],"timestamp":1775812272434}}
