{"type":"message","id":"f447d1c1","parentId":"a682688a","timestamp":"2026-04-10T16:30:49.101Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Once upon a time, a little girl named Wilma was born in Tennessee. When she was just a baby, she got very sick — double pneumonia and scarlet fever left her legs paralyzed. Doctors told her mother she might never walk again.\n\nShe had to wear a metal brace just to move. Every week, her mom took her on long bus rides for therapy. At age 9, she removed the brace. By 13, she developed a rhythmic walk.\n\nShe wanted to be a runner. She entered every race she could — and came in LAST every time. People told her to quit.\n\nBut she remembered how hard it was just to learn to walk. She kept running, training, trying.\n\nAnd then — she won. Then she won again. And again.\n\nThat little girl who was told she'd never walk became the fastest woman in the world, winning THREE Olympic gold medals.\n\nThe lesson? When life pushes you down, get back up. Keep going. Your breakthrough is coming.\n\nGoodnight! 🖤"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775838649098}}
